title: Israelis protest Netanyahu's legal overhaul plans for ninth week in a row
description: Tens of thousands of Israelis have taken to the streets in a ninth week of protests against Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's controversial plans to overhaul the country's legal system.

title: Protests break out in Iran over suspected poisoning of schoolgirls
description: Protests have broken out in Iran's capital Tehran after hundreds of girls were suspected to have been poisoned in dozens of schools.

title: Thousands march in Tunisia against food prices and president's crackdown on critics
description: Thousands of people have marched through Tunisia's capital, protesting against an expanding crackdown on opposition voices and a proposed lifting of subsidies for food and other goods.

title: Australia's 'biggest drug bust' stops £500m of cocaine from entering country
description: Australian police have intercepted $1bn Australian dollars worth of cocaine from entering the west of the country, in what is believed to be the nation's biggest-ever drug bust.

title: Undercover officer who hunted drug dealers reveals 'terrifying' violence he faced - and the secret he kept from family
description: Being bitten by drug dealers and stabbed with syringes "went with the territory" for undercover police officer Michael O'Sullivan.
